# 8lee.ai Cursor Rules

**CLAUDE.md is the canonical technical resource** - Always reference it first.

## Documentation Hierarchy

- **CLAUDE.md** - Technical canonical (commands, workflow, coding rules, references)
- **README.md** - Architecture, design system, tech stack (source of truth)
- **docs/00-ROADMAP.md** - Active TODOs and future work (ONLY place for plans)
- **docs/release-notes/** - Weekly development logs
- **app/experiments/_docs/00-experiments-readme.md** - Experiments guide

## Quick Reference

**Runtime:** Bun 1.3.3 only (never npm/yarn/pnpm)

**Quality Checks:** Run `/check` command or `bunx tsc --noEmit && bunx biome check --write . && bun test`

**Design System:** Run `/design` for 11-point compliance audit (see README.md)

**Styling:** Tailwind v4 utilities only, shadcn/ui components, zero inline styles, zero custom classes

**Testing:** Focus on user intent and business logic, not implementation details

**Documentation:** No emojis in markdown files. See release notes protocol for content rules.

## Core Principles

- Prefer simple solutions using existing patterns
- Avoid duplication - check codebase first
- Fix issues without introducing new patterns/technologies
- Keep codebase clean and organized
- Reference documentation instead of recreating it

For complete rules and standards, see **CLAUDE.md**.

